##################################################
# Password method 0:
# Uncomment and edit password entries to set it via plain text.
# Password method 1:
# Add the password to the system keyring, and let msmtp get it automatically
# from the keyring as follows.
# To set the keyring password using Gnome's libsecret, do the following and
# enter password on prompt:
# $ secret-tool store --label=msmtp host smtp.gmail.com service smtp user osamu.aoki@gmail.com
# To do the same with the visible password entry and erasing its shell history:
# $ echo -n "secretword" | secret-tool store --label=msmtp host smtp.gmail.com service smtp user osamu.aoki@gmail.com
# $ history -c && history -w
